<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1379,1729]" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">
We did not examine any specimens of this species, since they are difficult to access. According to the figures in the original description in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lahiri, A. R." box="[407,560,1415,1441]" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" pagination="119 - 132" refId="ref14277" refString="Lahiri, A. R. (1979) Odonata (Insecta) from different states of north Eastern India. Oriental Insects, 13, 119 - 132. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1979.10433550" type="journal article" year="1979">Lahiri (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, this species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[828,927,1415,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[828,927,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Asahina, S." box="[941,1128,1414,1441]" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref13502" refString="Asahina, S. (1985 b) Contributions to the taxonomic knowledge of the Megalestes species of continental South Asia (Odonata, Synlestidae). Cho-Cho, 8 (10), 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1985">Asahina (1985b)</bibRefCitation>
put character figures of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lahiri" authorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lieftincki">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. lieftincki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[415,514,1451,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[415,514,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but provided no figure of the ligula for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[971,1032,1451,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[971,1032,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Asahina, S." box="[1046,1234,1450,1477]" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref13502" refString="Asahina, S. (1985 b) Contributions to the taxonomic knowledge of the Megalestes species of continental South Asia (Odonata, Synlestidae). Cho-Cho, 8 (10), 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1985">Asahina (1985b)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide a key, and some emphasized characters, such as “disk-shaped” basal tooth of cerci with “bush of hairs” on the apex, actually exist in both species. Only one distinct character separates 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lahiri" authorityYear="1979" box="[920,1056,1523,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lieftincki">
<emphasis box="[920,1056,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. lieftincki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[1127,1227,1523,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[1127,1227,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
if the drawings in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lahiri, A. R." box="[151,301,1559,1585]" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" pagination="119 - 132" refId="ref14277" refString="Lahiri, A. R. (1979) Odonata (Insecta) from different states of north Eastern India. Oriental Insects, 13, 119 - 132. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1979.10433550" type="journal article" year="1979">Lahiri (1979)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Asahina, S." box="[353,540,1558,1585]" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref13502" refString="Asahina, S. (1985 b) Contributions to the taxonomic knowledge of the Megalestes species of continental South Asia (Odonata, Synlestidae). Cho-Cho, 8 (10), 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1985">Asahina (1985b)</bibRefCitation>
are credible, that is, the dorsal side of S10 is flat (rare in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[1176,1302,1559,1585]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1176,1302,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">Megalestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lahiri" authorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lieftincki">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. lieftincki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but swelling in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[388,487,1595,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[388,487,1595,1621]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis box="[502,525,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M</emphasis>
egalestes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[633,694,1595,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[633,694,1595,1621]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is limited to the 
<collectingRegion box="[886,958,1595,1621]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">Fujian</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1013,1113,1595,1621]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
provinces of 
<collectingCountry box="[1267,1334,1595,1621]" name="China" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">China</collectingCountry>
which is about 
<quantity box="[221,321,1631,1657]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" unit="km" value="2000.0">2000 km</quantity>
away from the 
<typeStatus box="[500,548,1631,1657]" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lahiri" authorityYear="1979" box="[678,815,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lieftincki">
<emphasis box="[678,815,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. lieftincki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This makes it unlikely that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lahiri" authorityYear="1979" box="[1138,1275,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lieftincki">
<emphasis box="[1138,1275,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. lieftincki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[209,308,1667,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[209,308,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">M. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for which reason we regard it to be a good species. Nonetheless a more detailed description, if possible combined with genetic data, would be valuable.
</paragraph>
